To center a div in CSS, you can use `margin: auto` with a defined width, or use flexbox. Example:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}
```

Flexbox is a CSS layout model that allows easy alignment of items. Example:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}
```.

CSS Grid is a powerful layout system. Example:
```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
}
```.

